TiaMoko Entrepreneurship & Leadership Centre joined the Ministry of Entrepreneurship , FNB Botswana , Human Resource Professional Society Botswana, Local Enterprise Authority , Botswana Agricultural Marketing Board - BAMB , HRDC, Nonofo Dube-Jesse and other organizations at the Botswana University of Agriculture and Natural Resources (BUAN) at the inaugural Marketplace Drive Event. The esteemed event served as a platform for students to gain valuable insights and experiences from industry leaders as they transitioned from academia to the professional world. TiaMoko was a distinguished invitee at this momentous occasion, sharing their knowledge and expertise with the graduating students.

Botswana University of Agriculture & Natural Resources students left the Marketplace Drive Event with a wealth of knowledge on how to apply for jobs, what to include in their Curriculum Vitae, interview tips, soft skills and Competencies as well as valuable career branding tools to help them effectively communicate their value to potential employers.

EMPLOYMENT WORKSHOP 2.0: Strategies for Success in the Modern Workplace

TiaMoko is pleased to present Employment Workshop 2.0, an event designed to equip attendees with the skills and knowledge necessary to thrive in today's competitive job market. Our esteemed speakers, Segofalang Nagafela-Bibiza , a highly regarded HR consultant and mental health activist, and Raymond Mapena , a successful entrepreneur and inspirational speaker, will deliver insightful presentations on a range of important topics.

The workshop will cover a variety of essential subjects, including winning CV and cover letter writing, effective interview techniques, smart work ethics, strategies for switching between jobs, positioning yourself for promotion at work, staying relevant in the workplace to avoid retrenchment, and overcoming toxicity in the workplace. In addition, Raymond Mapena will provide valuable guidance on side hustles to improve your income streams and discovering your God-given purpose to reach your full potential.

Tickets are available at the following prices:
Early Bird Ticket-P120.00
Standard ticket-P150.00
Double ticket-P250.00.

GET YOUR TICKET NOW: 74121571

Don't miss this unique opportunity to learn from experts in their fields and gain valuable insights into achieving success in your career. Join us at Employment Workshop 2.0!
